# 🚀 Green Spark Submission


Tech for Cleaner and Greener Communities
Ecoswap

## Problem Statement Addressed
"How might we build and deploy technology-driven solutions that actively promote cleaner, greener communities and environmental sustainability?"

## Project Overview
A simple website where people in the community can:

List items they want to donate or swap (e.g., clothes, books, electronics)

Browse items others have listed

Contact details can be optional or kept private (you can skip actual messaging)

## Key Features
1.Extremely Simple and Lightweight : Yours works instantly, no login, no signup — just list and view items. It's perfect for local or temporary use (college, community events).

2. Local and Community-Focused
You can design your version to work only for your school, college, apartment, or city — not global.
This makes it more personal and manageable.

3.Focused on All Types of Reusable Items :-Focus on non-food items like books, clothes, or electronics.
Target youth, students, or eco clubs.
Be used for pop-up reuse events, such as donation drives or semester-end clearouts.

